(94, '127', '127', 'NIKE DUNK LOW OFF-WHITE LOT 42 ', '65000', '65000', '', 'dunk-low', NULL, 'Virgil Abloh and Nike continue their creative partnership with the Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 42, part of the expansive \'Dear Summer\' collection that follows Abloh\'s initial Nike Dunk collaboration in 2019. This low-top sneaker showcases a white leather upper with soft grey canvas overlays, embodying Abloh\'s distinctive design approach. The iconic plastic zip tie and Helvetica text on the tongue add a signature touch.\r\n\r\nThe Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 42 features vibrant accents throughout, including the supplementary lacing system, zip-tie, exposed-foam tongue, and rectangular tab attached to the Swoosh. The design embodies Off-White\'s ethos of exploring the \"grey area between black and white.\" Limited to just fifty pairs, the shoe is marked with a \'42 of 50\' badge on the lateral midsole, highlighting its exclusivity.\r\n\r\nOriginally introduced as a collegiate sneaker, Nike Dunks have gained popularity among both celebrities and sneaker enthusiasts worldwide. The Off White Dunks, stemming from the 2019 collaboration between Nike and Virgil Abloh\'s Off-White label, have solidified their place in sneaker culture as highly sought-after collector\'s items.\r\n\r\nFor the latest Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks, and other limited edition sneakers, explore the wide selection available at House of Sneakers.', 'SAIL/NEUTRAL GREY-LIGHT BONE', NULL, '2023-06-28 02:53', 1),
(95, '128', '128', 'NIKE DUNK LOW OFF-WHITE LOT 33', '65000', '65000', '', 'dunk-low', NULL, 'The Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 33 showcases a stylish combination of cream-white leather and grey suede materials. The cream-white leather is prominently featured on the toe box, mid-panel underlay, and parts of the heel, while the grey suede overlays can be found on the toe, vamp, mid-panel to the eyestay placket, Swoosh symbol, back-quarter, and heel.\r\n\r\nPaying tribute to Off-WhiteTM\'s branding, the Nike logo is positioned vertically along the side of the soft pink mesh tongue, creating a unique visual effect with a carved-out hole. Additionally, the Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 33 features red rope laces that adorn the entire top of the shoe, purely for decorative purposes, as the regular \"SHOELACES\" are still present along the tongue. This sought-after sneaker also incorporates Virgil Abloh\'s signature elements, such as a rubber green marble-effect midsole plug that signifies the pair\'s specific number.\r\n\r\nInitially released as a collegiate sneaker, Nike Dunks have now gained widespread popularity among both celebrities and sneaker enthusiasts worldwide. The Off White Dunks, born out of the collaborative efforts between Nike and Virgil Abloh\'s Off-White label in 2019, have solidified their position in sneaker culture as coveted collector\'s items.\r\n\r\nFor the latest releases of Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks, and other limited edition sneakers, explore the exclusive collection available at House of Sneakers. The Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 33 is presented in the captivating color combination of SAIL/NEUTRAL GREY-CHILE RED.', ' SAIL/NEUTRAL GREY-CHILE RED', NULL, '2023-06-28 02:55', 1),
(96, '129', '129', 'NIKE DUNK LOW OFF-WHITE LOT 40', '65000', '65000', '', 'dunk-low', NULL, 'The Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 40 is an exciting addition to the extensive \'Dear Summer\' collection, which builds upon Virgil Abloh\'s initial collaboration with Nike in 2019. This particular model is part of Off-White\'s current project, which focuses on a single low-top Nike Dunk silhouette and presents it in an array of 48 different colorways for various elements like the lace, tongue, sock-liner, zip tie, lot numbering, and lateral swoosh layer.\r\n\r\nThe Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 40 showcases a white leather upper complemented by soft grey suede accents, staying true to Virgil Abloh\'s distinctive design aesthetic. The sneaker incorporates notable details such as a plastic zip tie and Helvetica text imprinted on the tongue. The additional lacing system, zip-tie, exposed-foam tongue, and rectangular tab, all attached to the Swoosh, feature vibrant pops of color, adding a visually striking element to the shoe. Limited to just fifty pairs, the Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 40 bears a \'40 of 50\' badge on the lateral midsole, signifying its exclusivity.\r\n\r\nOriginally introduced as a collegiate sneaker, Nike Dunks have gained popularity among both celebrities and everyday individuals. The Off White Dunks, born out of the 2019 collaboration between Nike and Virgil Ablohâ€™s Off-White label, have become highly sought-after collector\'s items, further solidifying the Dunk\'s place in sneaker folklore.\r\n\r\nTo stay up-to-date with the latest releases of Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks, and other limited edition sneakers, be sure to explore the exclusive collection available at House of Sneakers.', ' WHITE/NEUTRAL GREY-FUCHSIA-TRUE BERRY', NULL, '2023-06-28 02:57', 1),
(97, '130', '130', 'NIKE DUNK LOW OFF-WHITE LOT 38', '65000', '65000', '', 'dunk-low', NULL, 'The Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 38 is a part of the \'Dear Summer\' collection, which expands upon the initial collaboration between Nike and Virgil Abloh in 2019. Unlike the first and last numbers in the series, Lot 1 and Lot 50, this specific iteration falls into the range of 48 Dunks with a grey color scheme. The design of the Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 38 embodies Off-White\'s vision of exploring the \"grey region between black and white,\" as described by Virgil Abloh.\r\n\r\nThis low-top sneaker features a white leather upper accompanied by soft grey suede overlays, staying true to Virgil Abloh\'s distinct aesthetic. The signature details of the Off-White x Nike collaboration are present, including a plastic zip tie and Helvetica text printed on the tongue. Vibrant pops of color adorn the alternative lacing system, zip tie, exposed-foam tongue, and rectangular tab attached to the Swoosh, adding eye-catching elements to the design. Limited to only fifty pairs, the Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 38 is marked with a \'38 of 50\' badge on the lateral midsole, symbolizing its exclusivity.\r\n\r\nOriginally released as a collegiate sneaker, Nike Dunks have gained widespread popularity among celebrities and individuals from all walks of life. The Off White Dunks, born out of the 2019 collaboration between Nike and Virgil Ablohâ€™s Off-White label, have become iconic and highly sought-after, solidifying the Dunk\'s place in sneaker culture.\r\n\r\nFor the latest releases of Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks, and other limited edition sneakers, visit House of Sneakers. ', 'WHITE/NEUTRAL GREY-GOLDENROD-SHY BLUE', NULL, '2023-06-28 02:59', 1),
(98, '131', '131', 'NIKE DUNK LOW OFF-WHITE LOT 45', '55000', '55000', 'nike-dunk-low-off-white-lot-45', 'dunk-low', NULL, 'The Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 45 is a remarkable collaboration between Nike and Virgil Abloh, showcasing their iconic design aesthetics.\r\n\r\nCrafted with attention to detail, the Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 45 combines a sail white and neutral grey upper, constructed from premium materials such as leather and suede overlays. Virgil Abloh\'s signature elements, including the plastic zip tie and printed Helvetica text on the tongue, add a distinctive touch.\r\n\r\nThe standout feature of this shoe is the vibrant pops of alpha orange seen on the supplementary lacing system, zip tie, exposed-foam tongue, and rectangular tab attached to the Swoosh. These contrasting accents create a bold and eye-catching look.\r\n\r\nLimited to just fifty pairs, the Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 45 is a highly coveted collector\'s item. It is adorned with a \'45 of 50\' badge on the lateral midsole, emphasizing its exclusivity and rarity.\r\n\r\nThe Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 45 is an exceptional release that showcases the innovative partnership between Nike and Virgil Abloh. Its unique color combination and premium construction make it a must-have for sneaker enthusiasts.\r\n\r\nFor the latest releases of Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks, and other limited edition sneakers, visit House of Sneakers.', 'SAIL/NEUTRAL GREY-ALPHA ORANGE', '10 size', '2023-06-28 03:06', 1),
(99, '133', '133', 'NIKE SB DUNK LOW WHAT THE PAUL', '65000', '65000', '', 'sb-dunk', NULL, 'The Nike SB Dunk Low What The Paul pays tribute to the legendary skateboarder Paul Rodriguez and his remarkable legacy with Nike Skateboarding. As the proud owner of ten signature sneakers, Paul Rodriguez is an iconic figure in the world of skateboarding.\r\n\r\nThis special edition sneaker combines elements from the most iconic colorways of Paul Rodriguez\'s previous collaborations, creating a visually captivating and diverse design. Each shoe features mismatched make-ups, showcasing distinctive components from his collection. The upper is composed of various materials, including mesh, leather, suede, patent leather, and woven fabrics, resulting in a textured and dynamic look.\r\n\r\nThe Nike SB Dunk Low What The Paul stands out with its ornate embroidery, wild designs, and colorful gradients. It celebrates the rich history behind every material, design, and hue that Paul Rodriguez has experienced throughout his partnership with Nike Skateboarding. The shoe also features Paul Rodriguez\'s signature on the tongue and unique edition metal deubrÃ©s, adding a personal touch.\r\n\r\nWhile Nike SB originated in skateboarding, it draws inspiration from the world of basketball as well. The Dunk Low silhouette, with its black toe-style color-blocking and Boston Celtics-inspired palette of black, white, and green, pays homage to both skateboarding and basketball. The shoe is designed with a padded tongue and a Zoom Air-cushioned sole to provide comfort and support for skateboarding activities.\r\n\r\nThe Nike SB Dunk series, introduced in 2002, was specifically engineered for skateboarding, featuring enhanced padding and improved traction. It quickly became a canvas for experimentation, incorporating unconventional color combinations and unique fabrics like pig suede.\r\n\r\nFor the latest releases of Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks, and other limited edition sneakers, you can find them at House of Sneakers.', 'color- blocked', NULL, '2023-06-28 03:10', 1),
(100, '134', '134', 'NIKE DUNK HIGH AMBUSH BLACK WHITE', '65000', '65000', 'nike-dunk-high-ambush-black-white', 'dunk-high', NULL, 'The Nike Dunk High Ambush Black White is a collaboration between Nike and Tokyo-based fashion brand AMBUSH, known for its avant-garde and abstract designs. This sneaker takes the classic Dunk High silhouette and adds unique elements to create a distinctive look.\r\n\r\nThe upper of the shoe features a color-blocked design in white and black leather, reminiscent of the original Nike Dunk releases from 1985. One of the standout features is the oversized Swoosh, which extends beyond the heel, giving it a bold and exaggerated appearance. The heel counter is elevated and showcases noticeable separation, with a greater amount of white leather paneling and an expanded black plastic unit with Ambush branding. These design elements set this collaboration apart from the traditional Nike Dunks and contribute to its reimagined aesthetic.\r\n\r\nAdditional details include an exposed foam tongue, a white sole, and a tongue tag that bears the branding of both Nike and AMBUSH. The overall design concept draws inspiration from the expanded tailpipes and raised rear chassis of motorbikes and trucks, creating a unique visual connection to the world of automotive design.\r\n\r\nNike Dunks have become popular not only among athletes but also among celebrities and sneaker enthusiasts. The release of limited editions, such as the Off White Dunks from the collaboration with Virgil Abloh\'s Off-White label in 2019, has further solidified the Dunk\'s status in sneaker culture.\r\n\r\nTo stay updated on the latest releases of Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks, and other limited edition sneakers, you can visit House of Sneakers.', 'WHITE/BLACK', 'UK 10', '2023-06-28 03:12', 1),
(101, '135,134,133', '135', 'NIKE SB DUNK LOW J-PACK CHICAGO', '60000', '60000', 'nike-sb-dunk-low-j-pack-chicago', 'sb-dunk', NULL, 'The Nike SB Low J-Pack Chicago, like several other Nike silhouettes, has found its way from the basketball court to the feet of skateboarders over the company\'s history. Skaters and basketball players alike seek kicks with many of the same characteristics: maximum traction, adaptable cushioning, and low force upon landing. Skaters in the 1980s and 1990s preferred to skate in Air Jordan 1s before there were so many options for decent skateboarding footwear. The high-top structure of the sneaker provides the necessary ankle support for numerous skateboarding maneuvers. The latest iteration of the Nike SB Dunk J-Pack pays homage to the Air Jordan 1\'s early skate culture involvement.\r\n\r\nThe Nike SB Dunk Low J-Pack is dressed in a colour palette made popular by a high-flying superstar who earned his name in the Windy City, and this release pays homage to those historical ties. To complete this traditional look, the classic colours of Varsity Red are combined with neutral touches of black and white. It provides something for both Jordan and Super Bowl fans. The skateboarding feature of the sneaker is then introduced via a large tongue and oval laces.\r\n\r\nNike took note of the love skaters had for the Dunk and finally in 2002, introduced the SB Dunk, re-engineered for skating with features such as more padding and better traction. The SB Dunk became a canvas to try out offbeat colour combinations and unusual fabrics like pig suede.\r\n\r\nGet the latest Nike Dunks, Nike SB Dunks and more limited edition sneakers only on House of Sneakers.\r\n\r\n', 'RED/WHITE/BLACK', '<?php echo $row[\'size\']; ?>', '2023-06-28 03:16', 1),
